                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="472352" author="emoly.liu" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2025 03:22:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rread&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rread&quot;&gt;rread&lt;/a&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Would these functions work on any client, like&#160;&lt;tt&gt;llapi_hsm_copytool_register()&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have added a new RPC MDS_CHANGELOG_GET_USER_INFO in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19296&quot; title=&quot;changelog processing should use per-user state&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19296&quot;&gt;LU-19296&lt;/a&gt; to get changelog user information from MDT to client for changelog filtering. Next, I will improve these APIs with new RPCs, then they will work on client.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471749" author="emoly.liu" created="Wed, 17 Sep 2025 07:03:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471736" author="adilger" created="Wed, 17 Sep 2025 04:30:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Emoly, can you please take over the patch.  I think it is mostly complete, but I need to focus on the EC HLD and I don&apos;t want this patch to sit idle.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471735" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 17 Sep 2025 04:27:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61340&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61340&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19276&quot; title=&quot;add llapi_changelog_register() and llapi_changelog_deregister() functions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19276&quot;&gt;LU-19276&lt;/a&gt; llapi: add llapi_changelog_(de)register&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: eee2cf106d775e99c2f05883c2dd73cc7d4f6c1a&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="468689" author="adilger" created="Sun, 24 Aug 2025 01:20:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Currently the &quot;lctl changelog_register/deregister&quot; only run on the MDS. This used to be a limited access request because there is overhead on the MDS when a Changelog user is registered, and it could cause the MDT to run out of space. However, with automatic Changelog garbage collection this should be less of an issue and we might be ok to do this in the future. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="468606" author="rread" created="Fri, 22 Aug 2025 12:20:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would these functions work on any client, like &lt;tt&gt;llapi_hsm_copytool_register()&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
